## My process

### Built with

- Semantic HTML5 markup
- CSS custom properties
- Flexbox
- CSS Grid
- Mobile-first workflow
  -styles
  -React

### What I learned

Continued developing my understanding of position: absolute and position: relative, and how they can be used to control layout and positioning in CSS.
Explored usability concepts in React through the design and implementation of custom buttons.

### Continued development

Continue improving my SCSS skills by writing cleaner, more accessible, and maintainable code that is easier to scale, follow, and debug.
Focus on creating more consistent spacing and padding across different screen sizes to improve responsiveness and the overall user experience.
Continue learning and developing my React skills, as I enjoy working with it and want to deepen my understanding of component-based development and state management.

### Useful resources

-MDN Web Docs — A reliable resource for learning CSS, SCSS, React, and modern web development concepts.
Sass Documentation — Helped me understand SCSS features such as variables, nesting, mixins, and code organisation.
React Documentation — Useful for learning React concepts, components, state management, hooks, and best practices.

### AI Collaboration

I used ChatGPT to help debug some silly CSS and React issues, understand concepts such as positioning.ChatGPT was helpful for explaining concepts, troubleshooting errors, and suggesting alternative approaches when I was stuck.
What didn't work: Some suggestions required further testing and adjustment to fit my project's specific requirements. I still needed to verify solutions and ensure they followed best practices for my implementation.

